The paper deals with decoding algorithms for convolutional codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory community (cs.IT). The use of statistical learning techniques is also a prominent feature of the paper, which suggests a possible fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of complexity and delay, which are relevant topics in the computer networks (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed algorithm with other coding schemes, which is a common theme in the coding theory (cs.CC) sub-category.
